  "texts": [
    "We call a k-current flat, or a flat chain, if it lies inF k (K) for some compact K ⊂ R d.Next, we identify flat chains in the top dimension.",
    "The symbol L d stands for the Lebesgue measure.",
    "Via (2.1), given a d-form ω, there exists a unique real valued map which we, using abuse of notation, denote again by ω, such thatω = ωdx 1 ∧ • • • ∧ dx d. Lemma 2.2.",
    "Suppose Q ⊂ R d is compact, convex and has non-empty interior.",
    "Then the mapL 1 (Q) ∋ φ → (ω → φω dL d) ∈ F d (Q)is an isometry of Banach spaces.In light of the previous lemma, we may simply identifyF d (Q) = L 1 (Q).Given T ∈ F k (K) and a smooth map F: R d → R m, one can define the pushforward of T by F, denoted by F # T. The definition is given byF # T (ωdx i 1 ∧ • • • ∧ dx i k) = T (η(ω • F)dF i 1 ∧ • • • ∧ dF i k) for ω ∈ C ∞ c (R m), where η is any smooth, compactly supported function, which is equal to 1 on a neighbourhood of F (spt T)."
